Implementation of the CommandMediator class. This class is purposed to be a SPOT (Single Point Of Truth) utility that executes and profiles (optionally) commands. This class provides a single point for serial/parallel commands, general logging, command logging and exception handling/logging. It also provides events to the UI layer that notify it when commands are running and completed.

detaileddescription.para: Copyright: Created by Tony Jenniges, 2008-2009, All rights reserved.

Advantages of CommandMediator SPOT (Single Point Of Truth) utility that can be used on multiple projects (and battle tested and hardened). Common point for application logging Common point for application exception handling Command performance profiling and reporting Multi-threaded command execution. Less implementation code in GUI (i.e., 'thin' client UI)
